(2) If any condition, imposed under the provisions of subsection (2) of section five, or of paragraph (b) of subsection (1), or of subsection (5) of section eight, is broken, each of the promoters of the lottery concerned and, where the person by whom the condition is broken is not one of the promoters, that person also, shall be guilty of an offence and shall be liable to a fine not exceeding two hundred and fifty penalty units Provided that it shall be a defence for a person charged only by reason of his being a promoter of the lottery to prove that the offence was committed without his knowledge. [As amended by No. 20 of 1961, G.N. No. 304 of 1964 and Act No. 13 of 1994 ]
