Without prejudice to the generality of paragraph (b) of subsection (1) of section six, a controlling authority may, in respect of any lottery authorised by it, impose conditions under the said paragraph—
(a) providing for the amount, not exceeding twelve and one-half per centum of the gross proceeds of the lottery , which the promoters thereof may deduct from such proceeds in respect of operating expenses; Provided that, in the case of a series of lotteries proposed to be promoted by the same persons, the authority may, in its discretion, allow the deduction of an amount in excess of the aforesaid percentage in respect of all or any of the lotteries drawn within the period of twelve months from the date of the draw of the first lottery in such series;
